Activation tool notes:

1)  Each activation tool needs to be run as "Administrator" - Right-click --> Run as administrator

2)  Activator 1.5 and Toolkit 1.8 use "frankenbuild" methods, which use hacks to inject RC code/keys and activate them, hence the possible addition of expiration dates (run WINVER)

3)  TimerNuke nukes the activation pieces altogether, so activation status stays at "unknown"

4)  ALL activation hacks should be considered temporary, as Microsoft deploys countermeasures against them - YMMV

5)  Doubful anything will be permanent (unless you don't update your OS and keep it off Internet)...OEM methods will have the best chance at success

@bv_abhi:  This is indeed the final version.  You will need to decide, however, how to deal with activation.  Using the included toolkit WILL render your OS crippled on 3/2/2010 due to expiration of the RC key hack.  Nobody has their hands on final Windows 7 license keys, and if they did, they would be foolish to share, as mass activations on a particular key would render the key useless.

Hi guys, I will try to answer some questions so you don't have to crawl through every comment page to find it. (Please note that my answers may be inaccurate, if not entirely wrong, so use it at your own discretion.)

@ XecutionerZ
Q: "N about activation...,does it work..???"
A: After downloading and installing this torrent (smoothly), using the activator included DID NOT work. It may just be my comp, and that it could work on others, but it did not work for me at all. 

After a while googling around, I found this activator to work perfectly: http://keznews.com/5968_Windows_7_RTM_7600_x86_and_x64_activator_-_time_crack

I used "Windows 7 7600 x86 and x64 activator (link 1)". After downloading and extracting it (the file is in .rar format), run "Windows_7_Build_7600_Activator". If you are using Vista, please remember to right click it and "Run as administrator". Click the activate button, and it should activate this Windows 7 copy. To check/make sure it did indeed work, click "Start" and type in "activate" in the search bar. Click on "Activate Windows 7" and it will display whether it has been activated or not.

@ fugitiv3
Q: "is this bootable?"
A: Never tried, HOWEVER, when I restarted my computer with the disc still in the drive (I burned the .iso to a disc) there was a screen that asked if I wanted to boot anything from the disc. So the option was there, but I never tried it to see if it works.

@ sanderb134
Q: "is this a clean install or an upgrade?"
A: You can either do a clean install OR an upgrade. However, it will not allow you to upgrade if you are currently using Windows XP.

@ jag_tadeos
Q: "WinRar is asking the password to unpack this stuff, could someone able to give the password please? thanks."
A: The torrent is not in .rar format and doesn't need a password.

@ lars66157
Q: "does this work? is this the real windows 7?
does these version never start up during run this?"
A: Yes it works, it is the real Windows 7, and hasn't failed to startup/shutdown for me yet.

@ Odracir194
Q: "Will windows update work on it?"
A: Yes it does, just activate Windows 7. So far, I have only used Windows Update to download some "Optional Updates".

@ yomo68 
Q: "is this better than xp for games.. if yes i'll download"
A: For me, it seems that games run just a tiny bit smoother. Not a big difference. However, other users have stated that their fps (frames per second) in games have increased by a lot.

FAQ: "Can I please have a key to activate Windows 7 Build 7600 (RTM)?"
A: As of right now, there are no available keys to activate it. There are methods to change the files of the RTM into the RC and use the RC keys to activate.

FAQ: "Will Windows 7 Build 7600 (RTM) expire?"
A: No, but without the keys (or activation), it will be unusable after 30 days. 

FAQ: "Is this .iso touched? Or untouched?
A: I have no idea, but two previous comments have stated that "Wzor" has touched it. It's perfectly fine, as the torrent is clean (no viruses/trojans/spyware).

FAQ: "Is this the actual RTM? I thought it wouldn't come out till October 22nd?"
A: It has been heavily speculated (even confirmed by some sources) that Build 7600.163.85 is indeed the RTM that Microsoft will ship out on October 22nd.
